title: Agostinho. (Ilhéu de)
body: The three islets known as Agostinho, dos Desembarcadouros, and Fora are considered an extension of Ponta de S. Lourenço (see this name). The first is the closest to the actual Point and is separated from it by a small channel or passage. Next is the Islet of Desembarcadouros (see this name), followed by the Islet of Fora (see this name). Agostinho is the smallest and least important of the three islets adjacent to Ponta de São Lourenço. At low tide, it is possible to wade through the narrow passage that separates the small islet from the mentioned Point.

Ponta de S. Lourenço: Extension of Ponta de S. Lourenço
